# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# THE www FIX: send every www.* request to the canonical apex, preserving path.
# This makes typing www.quincythebedlington.com land on the real site.
https://www.quincythebedlington.com/* https://quincythebedlington.com/:splat 301

# Force HTTPS on the apex (Cloudflare usually also handles this via Always Use HTTPS).
http://quincythebedlington.com/* https://quincythebedlington.com/:splat 301

# HIDE the free *.pages.dev URLs: bounce anyone who hits them to the real domain.
# Cloudflare always assigns a *.pages.dev host to every project and it can't be
# deleted, so we 301 it away instead. Each line only fires on its own host, so
# this single file is safe to deploy to BOTH the prod and dev projects.
# Production project -> apex.
https://quincythebedlington.pages.dev/* https://quincythebedlington.com/:splat 301
# Dev/staging project -> dev subdomain.
https://quincythebedlington-dev.pages.dev/* https://dev.quincythebedlington.com/:splat 301
